

# Goal
Design a smarter, context-aware AI for ChillBoard that correlates screen time, content type, and mood to make empathetic Spotify recommendations and new wellness features—solving the “long YouTube comedy ≠ stressed” mismatch.

# Improved AI Approach
- **Multi-signal stress likelihood (SL) score**
  - Inputs per session: `screen_time`, `content_mix` (comedy/education/drama/news/gaming/social/etc.), `content_sentiment` (title/description), `engagement` (scroll/click density), `time_of_day`, `app_diversity`, `recent_mood` (self/face-api), `sleep/movement` (optional), `unlock_freq`.
  - Compute features:
    - **Duration features**: total minutes, streak length, circadian context.
    - **Content features**: per-category share, entropy (diversity), “work-load” index (docs/editing/IDE/ed-tech vs entertainment).
    - **Affect features**: sentiment/emotion from titles/metadata; recent self-report bias-corrected.
    - **Wellbeing features**: sleep debt proxy, inactivity (movement low), device unlock rate.
  - Model SL ∈ [0,1] via ensemble:
    - **Late-fusion** of sub-models: (1) duration-only, (2) content/emotion, (3) self-report/biometrics (optional).
    - Final calibrated probability (Platt/Isotonic) for interpretability.
- **Context-aware recommendations**
  - Map SL + context → music intent:
    - High SL + work context → calm/relax/focus.
    - Low SL + comedy/entertainment → upbeat/energy.
    - Night + tired → sleep/relax.
    - Long focus session + neutral → focus/lofi/chill-beats.
  - Use bandit-style exploration to personalize over time (small epsilon to try new categories).

# Features To Add
- **Content understanding**
  - Categorize visited pages by domain and YouTube video metadata (category/tags), title sentiment/emotion.
  - Topic embedding clustering to detect “work vs entertainment vs doomscrolling.”
- **Sentiment/emotion detection**
  - On titles/descriptions; optional transcript sentiment if available.
- **Context-aware recs**
  - Switch playlists by context (focus vs unwind vs energize), not only mood/duration.
- **Adaptive sessions**
  - Break suggestions with timers tuned by current SL and session type (study vs binge).
- **Personalization**
  - Learn user-specific response to playlist categories (reward = dwell time after rec, user thumbs-up, acceptance rate).
- **Explanations**
  - Show “Why this recommendation?” with top features that influenced SL.
- **Controls**
  - User can correct mood/context; weight corrections to retrain profile.

# Additional Self-Tracking Signals
- **Sleep**: manual entry or wearable import (duration, consistency).
- **Movement**: steps/proxy (web only → rough inactivity via idle/mouse/keyboard).
- **App usage diversity**: entropy index; low diversity + long duration can raise SL.
- **Journaling**: lightweight daily check-in; text sentiment for labels (on-device).
- **Device unlock frequency**: proxy for compulsive checking.
- **Notifications density**: spikes correlate with stress (if permissions granted).
- **Calendar load**: busy calendars correlate with higher SL (opt-in).

# Mismatch Detection Logic
- **Comedy binge example**
  - If `screen_time > threshold` AND `entertainment_share > 0.6` AND `content_sentiment >= neutral` AND `self_report != stressed` → down-weight stress; propose upbeat/relax, not calm-only.
- **Work sprint example**
  - `high screen_time` + `education/productivity domains` + `neutral/negative sentiment` + `late hours` → increase SL; propose calm/focus + short break.
- **Doomscrolling**
  - `news/social` + `negative sentiment` + `frequent unlocks` → elevate SL; propose mindful break + calming playlist.
- **Calibration**
  - Maintain **confidence** and **agreement score** across sub-models; only strong-confidence triggers auto-play, else suggest but do not autoplay.

# Multi-Modal AI Architecture
- **Ingestion (Extension + Backend)**
  - Extension logs tab time + URL; fetches YouTube category/title via API when possible; computes lightweight features; sends anonymized metadata (domain/category, not full URL).
- **Processing Pipeline**
  - Feature extraction service:
    - Text sentiment/emotion of titles/descriptions.
    - Categorization (taxonomy + embedding clustering).
    - Sessionization (burst detection, streaks).
- **Feature Store**
  - Daily aggregates, recent rolling windows (1h, 3h, 24h).
- **Model Service**
  - Submodels: Duration-only (baseline), Content-affect (Transformer/lexicon), Optional Face/Voice sentiment (on-device, opt-in).
  - Late fusion + calibration → SL score + context label.
- **Recommendation Engine**
  - Rules + bandit personalization:
    - Policy maps (SL, context, circadian) → music category + non-music nudge.
- **Feedback Loop**
  - Collect accepts/declines, post-play dwell, thumbs up/down to update user profile and bandit rewards.

## Suggested Model Types
- **Content Categorization**
  - TF-IDF + logistic regression (fast baseline) → upgrade to `sentence-transformers` embeddings + small classifier.
- **Sentiment/Emotion**
  - VADER/NRCLex (fast), upgrade to `cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment` or `j-hartmann/emotion-english-distilroberta-base` (HF).
- **Fusion/Scoring**
  - Gradient Boosted Trees (XGBoost/LightGBM) on engineered features; or small MLP with calibration.
- **Personalization**
  - Contextual bandits (LinUCB/Thompson) per user to pick playlist category.

## Training Tips
- **Labels**
  - Use self-reports (primary), weak labels from journaling/sentiment (secondary).
- **Bootstrapping**
  - Start with heuristics; log user feedback; retrain weekly.
- **Evaluation**
  - AUC/PR for SL; online A/B for acceptance rate, dwell time, and user-reported relief.
- **Calibration**
  - Isotonic/Platt scaling on validation for trustworthy SL.

# New User-Facing Features
- **Daily emotional summary**
  - Breakdown of context (work/entertainment), mood trends, top triggers, and suggested adjustments.
- **Activity–mood heatmap**
  - Calendar view showing SL by hour with predominant content type.
- **Positive content suggestions**
  - Recommend short positive/educational content when doomscrolling detected.
- **CBT/mindfulness coach**
  - Brief guided interventions; journaling prompts tied to detected context.
- **Burnout early warnings**
  - Notify if SL rising over multiple days; suggest schedule changes/rest blocks.
- **Break scheduler**
  - Auto-insert micro-break timers proportional to SL/session type.

# Privacy and Bias
- **Privacy-first**
  - On-device text inference where possible (TensorFlow.js/ONNX Runtime Web).
  - Send only anonymized metadata (domains/categories/titles hashed or stripped).
  - Clear opt-ins for webcam/voice; no raw media uploads; store mood strings only.
- **Bias control**
  - Regular audits for content-category bias (e.g., some genres flagged unfairly).
  - Per-user personalization over global assumptions; allow easy overrides.
  - Differential weighting for self-reports to reflect user uniqueness.

# Libraries and APIs
- **Content classification & sentiment**
  - Hugging Face Transformers, `sentence-transformers`, `cardiffnlp` models.
  - VADER, NRCLex (fast lexicon baselines).
  - spaCy + `en_core_web_sm` for NER/topics (lightweight).
- **On-device inference**
  - TensorFlow.js, ONNX Runtime Web.
- **YouTube metadata (optional)**
  - YouTube Data API v3 (video category, title, tags).
- **Embeddings search**
  - `faiss` or `qdrant` if you need efficient topic clustering at scale.
- **Bandits**
  - `mabwiser`, or implement LinUCB/Thompson in-house (simple).

# Prototype Plan (End-to-End)
- **Week 1: Feature scaffolding**
  - Extension: capture domain, estimated category (regex/domain mapping), YouTube title/category (if available); store locally; send anonymized metadata.
  - Backend: feature extraction service; store daily aggregates + 3h rolling windows.
- **Week 2: Baseline model**
  - Build engineered features; train LightGBM for SL using self-reports + weak labels; calibrate.
  - Implement policy mapping to playlist categories; add explanation strings.
- **Week 3: Frontend integration**
  - Show SL, confidence, and “why” explanation chips.
  - Update recommendation logic to use SL + context (focus/relax/upbeat/sleep/energy).
- **Week 4: Personalization**
  - Add bandit explorer to adapt category choice; collect rewards (accept/dwell).
- **Quality bar**
  - KPIs: +accept rate, +session relief (reduced SL or improved self-report), fewer “mismatch” flags.

# Context → Playlist Policy Examples
- **Work-heavy + high SL (daytime)** → `focus`, `calm`
- **Comedy/entertainment + low SL** → `upbeat`, `energy`
- **Night + tired** → [sleep](cci:1://file:///c:/Users/manik/Desktop/chillboard/ChillBoard-AI-Based-Digital-Wellness-Dashboard/ChillBoardExtension/background.js:97:0-99:1), `relax`
- **Doomscrolling news/social** → `calm`, short break task + breathing
- **Neutral + long session** → `focus`, `lofi`, micro-break reminder

# How This Solves “Comedy ≠ Stressed”
- We explicitly include content type + sentiment and reduce stress weighting if entertainment-positive dominates.
- SL is thus low despite long duration → no calm-only recs; instead upbeat/relax or a short stretch break.
- Explanations show: “Long session but comedy/positive; suggesting upbeat playlist.”

# Recommended Actions
- **[data collection]** Add content metadata capture in extension (category + sentiment-ready fields).
- **[backend]** Build feature extractor + calibrated SL service.
- **[recs]** Replace duration-only triggers with SL+context policy and bandit personalization.
- **[ui]** Add explainability chips and daily emotional summary.
- **[privacy]** Default to on-device text inference, anonymize any metadata.

# Summary
- Proposed a multi-modal, privacy-first AI that fuses duration, content type, sentiment, and self-reports to compute a calibrated stress score.
- Mismatch detection prevents false “stressed” when comedy dominates.
- Clear architecture, model choices, and a pragmatic prototype plan with future UX features and safety/bias controls.

